<Link id="l00070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="70"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// implement support for target specific assembly directives.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="71"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00072" /><CodeLine lineNumber="72"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// If target foo wants to use this, it should implement 3 classes:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00073" /><CodeLine lineNumber="73"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#42; FooTargetStreamer : public MCTargetStreamer</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00074" /><CodeLine lineNumber="74"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#42; FooTargetAsmStreamer : public FooTargetStreamer</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00075" /><CodeLine lineNumber="75"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#42; FooTargetELFStreamer : public FooTargetStreamer</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00076" /><CodeLine lineNumber="76"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00077" /><CodeLine lineNumber="77"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// FooTargetStreamer should have a pure virtual method for each directive. For</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00078" /><CodeLine lineNumber="78"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// example, for a &quot;.bar symbol&#95;name&quot; directive, it should have</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00079" /><CodeLine lineNumber="79"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// virtual emitBar(const MCSymbol &amp;Symbol) = 0;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00080" /><CodeLine lineNumber="80"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00081" /><CodeLine lineNumber="81"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The FooTargetAsmStreamer and FooTargetELFStreamer classes implement the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00082" /><CodeLine lineNumber="82"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// method. The assembly streamer just prints &quot;.bar symbol&#95;name&quot;. The object</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00083" /><CodeLine lineNumber="83"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// streamer does whatever is needed to implement .bar in the object file.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00084" /><CodeLine lineNumber="84"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00085" /><CodeLine lineNumber="85"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// In the assembly printer and parser the target streamer can be used by</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00087" /><CodeLine lineNumber="87"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00088" /><CodeLine lineNumber="88"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// MCTargetStreamer &amp;TS = OutStreamer.getTargetStreamer();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00089" /><CodeLine lineNumber="89"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// FooTargetStreamer &amp;ATS = static&#95;cast&lt;FooTargetStreamer &amp;&gt;(TS);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00090" /><CodeLine lineNumber="90"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00091" /><CodeLine lineNumber="91"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The base classes FooTargetAsmStreamer and FooTargetELFStreamer should</span></CodeLine>
